commit a27cd3734a26c7436074bcb9641fba93d1d92214 Author: Michal Domonkos <mdomonko@redhat.com> Date: Tue Dec 8 17:30:15 2015 +0100
Always match correct tsi on erasure (RhBug:1253120)
RPM callbacks only receive the package name on erasures. However, we need the package object, so we have to look it up ourselves. This was done by using the provided name but that didn't work correctly when multiple packages of the same name were being erased (e.g. multiple kernels); the lookup would always pick the first matching tsi that appeared in the transaction, ignoring the others.
This commit fixes that by making use of the new RPMCALLBACK_ELEM_PROGRESS type introduced to RPM by the commit baec562, allowing us to use NEVRA in the lookup instead.
